The paper deals with automated organ segmentation from 3D radiological scans using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper extensively uses holistically-nested convolutional networks (HNNs), which are a type of deep neural network, indicating that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the integration of semantic mid-level cues, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of 3D computed tomography (CT) volumes and medical image analysis suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
